The most evident external differences between the two species are: scutellum surrounded by dense and isolated pubescence (

O. zapotensis

) / scutellum not surrounded by dense pubescence, or the pubescence is not isolated (

O. mexicana

); dense pubescence on basal half of the elytra forming two isolated maculae, the first one inclined toward humerus (

O. zapotensis

) / dense pubescence on basal half of the elytra forming a longitudinal band with anterior area curved inward (

O. mexicana

). The study of the male genitalia of both species showed no difference between them.
